Once, there were two guilds almost constantly at war. The Ninjas
and the Thieves' guild were bitter enemies. Periodically, they
would halt their fighting for a time, and band together against
a common enemy. As soon as that enemy fell, and it always did
against their combined might, the two sides would once again
return to killing each other.

One day, a mighty force arrived, Timoban. More than a man, but
surely not a god, he took on both the thieves and the ninjas,
and defeated their mightiest leaders. The remaining thieves and
ninjas, unable to join forces, ever bickering and mistrustful
of each other, fell like sheep to the Solon.

Timoban, however, was impressed with the skill and powers of
the thieves and ninjas. He set about cleansing the two guilds,
making them one at their very core. He recruited some locals,
and showed them the new way, and then left, to conquer other
worlds.

The new Rogues, as Timoban called them, learned to keep to the
shadows, and not draw undue attention to themselves as did the
old Ninjas and Thieves, flaunting their power. To find, and
join them, you will need to look hard, or make subtle inquiries,
and perhaps they will find you instead.

The following races are restricted from Rogues:
Desert Dwarf, Stone Dwarf, Rift Duergar, Ice Ogre, and Barbarian.
